<i>noun</i>: 코너 [], 야단 [야ː단], 궁지 [궁지] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>코너 []</dt><br>
<dd>1. corner</dd><br>
<dd>구석이나 길의 모퉁이.</dd><br>
<dd>A hook or turn of a road.</dd><br>
<dd>2. department; section</dd><br>
<dd>백화점과 같은 큰 상가에서 특정한 상품을 진열하고 팔기 위한 곳.</dd><br>
<dd>A place to display and sell specific goods in a large store such as a department store.</dd><br>
<dd>3. corner; predicament</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 어떤 일이나 상황이 해결하기 어렵고 곤란하게 된 상태.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) The state in which a certain issue or situation has become difficult to solve.</dd><br>
<dd>4. page; program</dd><br>
<dd>신문이나 방송에서 일정한 것을 다루는 지면이나 프로그램.</dd><br>
<dd>A designated page of a newspaper or a designated program of broadcasting, that deals with a regular topic.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>야단 [야ː단]</dt><br>
<dd>1. uproar; tumult; clamor</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일 때문에 시끄럽게 자꾸 떠들거나 소란을 일으킴.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of making a noise or making a row due to something.</dd><br>
<dd>2. scolding; chiding; rebuke</dd><br>
<dd>다른 사람의 잘못을 큰소리로 혼냄.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of criticizing someone's mistake in a loud voice.</dd><br>
<dd>3. trouble; predicament; quandary</dd><br>
<dd>매우 곤란한 일.</dd><br>
<dd>A very awkward situation.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>궁지 [궁지]</dt><br>
<dd>predicament</dd><br>
<dd>매우 곤란한 처지.</dd><br>
<dd>A very difficult, vexing situation.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>